<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-11T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="548" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/8434</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-11T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 11, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3055. For <persName corresp="#p_COT1">Crosby</persName> [from
                                Treasury]:</p>
                            <p>Your No. 33 for Treasury. Regarding matter of tonnage and whether it
                                can be allocated for transport of troops you will please state that
                                that can be taken up in future when we are faced with practical
                                execution of plan. Please urge concurrence in principle on part of
                                both Governments and state that political situation in China will be
                                much improved by an evidence on part of Allies to allow her
                                cooperation even if practical difficulties actually prevent it.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>